data.name: VacationCalculation.Labels.MethodInformation
data.value:
Same wage rule is the default calculation method for an employee with fixed monthly salary 
 
 Percentage rule shall be used when an employee don’t have any fixed salary, for example is hourly paid. 
 An employee with fixed monthly salary shall use percentage rule when; 
 - variable salary components is more than 10% of the total salary 
 - part time factor has varied during vacation year 
 - employee’s part time factor during vacation earning year and currently vacation has varied
